==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Checkrein
<hw>Check"rein`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
short rein looped over the check hook to prevent a horse from lowering
his head; -- called also a <altname>bearing rein</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A branch rein connecting the driving rein of one
horse of a span or pair with the bit of the other horse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Checkroll</ent>⟦br⟧
